# Medplum Provider

A Terraform provider for [Medplum](https://www.medplum.com), an open-source FHIR R4 healthcare platform. Use it to declaratively manage FHIR resources, project structure, access policies, client applications, and user memberships ŌĆö the same objects you would otherwise manage through the Medplum app or API.

## Resources

### FHIR data

- [`medplum_fhir_resource`](./resources/fhir_resource.md) ŌĆö any FHIR R4 resource (ValueSet, Questionnaire, etc.)
- [`medplum_fhir_profile`](./resources/fhir_profile.md) ŌĆö FHIR R4 StructureDefinition (custom profile), with Medplum enforcement analysis at plan time

### Project structure

- [`medplum_project`](./resources/project.md) ŌĆö Medplum project (requires super-admin credentials)
- [`medplum_project_membership`](./resources/project_membership.md) ŌĆö bind a user or client application to a project with an access policy

### Access control

- [`medplum_access_policy`](./resources/access_policy.md) ŌĆö fine-grained resource-level access policy
- [`medplum_client_application`](./resources/client_application.md) ŌĆö OAuth client application with optional OIDC identity provider

### Users

- [`medplum_user`](./resources/user.md) ŌĆö Medplum user account

## Authentication

The provider supports three authentication modes; pick one:

| Mode | Arguments | Environment variables |
|---|---|---|
| Client credentials (recommended for automation) | `client_id`, `client_secret` | `MEDPLUM_CLIENT_ID`, `MEDPLUM_CLIENT_SECRET` |
| Bearer token (short-lived CI) | `access_token` | `MEDPLUM_ACCESS_TOKEN` |
| Super-admin email/password | `email`, `password` | `MEDPLUM_EMAIL`, `MEDPLUM_PASSWORD` |

Set `base_url` (or `MEDPLUM_BASE_URL`) to the address of your Medplum server.

## Quick start

```terraform
terraform {
  required_providers {
    medplum = {
      source  = "Fluent-Health/medplum"
      version = "~> 1.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "medplum" {
  base_url      = "https://medplum.example.com"
  client_id     = var.medplum_client_id
  client_secret = var.medplum_client_secret
}

resource "medplum_fhir_resource" "example_value_set" {
  resource_type = "ValueSet"

  body = jsonencode({
    resourceType = "ValueSet"
    url          = "https://example.com/fhir/ValueSet/blood-types"
    name         = "BloodTypes"
    status       = "active"
    compose = {
      include = [{
        system = "http://snomed.info/sct"
        concept = [
          { code = "112144000", display = "Blood group A" },
          { code = "165743006", display = "Blood group B" },
          { code = "46251000",  display = "Blood group AB" },
          { code = "58460004",  display = "Blood group O" },
        ]
      }]
    }
  })
}
```

